Question: Is your headache temporal?
Description: A severe, throbbing, and/or burning sensation at the temple on one or both sides of the head.

Question: Do you have any tenderness of the scalp?
Description: Scalp tenderness is defined as pain, inflammation, tingling, numbness, irritation, itching, throbbing, or sensitivity of the scalp.

Question: Do you have any jaw ﻿claudication?
Description: Jaw claudication is noted as fatigue or discomfort of the jaw muscles during chewing of firm foods such as meat, chewing gum, or prolonged speaking.

Question: Do you have any abnormal visual disturbances?
Any loss of vison?
Description: Vision loss is the degredation of your ability to see without some sort of vision correction in addition to any normal vision aids you may use.

Question: Is the loss of vision complete?
Description: Complete loss of vision in either eye is a degredation to the point you are unable to resolve objects even with the support of your usual vision corrective equipment.

Question: Is your loss of vision transient?
Description: Transient vision loss is a degredation to your usual vision that is temporary. It comes and goes, or it occurred once or twice for a brief period of time.

Question: Do you have any double vision?
Description: Double vision is a blurring or the appearance of multiple copies of the same object?

Question: Do you have any history of cerebrovascular accidents (stroke)?
Description: Cerebrovascular accident (CVA) is the medical term for a stroke. A stroke is when blood flow to a part of your brain is stopped either by a blockage or the rupture of a blood vessel.

Question: Do you have any constitutional type symptoms? (how do you feel generally)

Question: Is it ION?
